If your older brother does some crime, and he collects his loot in Bitcoin,=
 and the US government seizes his Bitcoin, and you steal the Bitcoin back o=
ut from under the government=E2=80=99s nose, and you convert the Bitcoin in=
to dollars, should you put the dollars into a bathtub and roll around in th=
em=C2=A0while women dance around you and your buddy takes pictures on your=
=C2=A0phone? I am not your lawyer and I am not going to give you legal advi=
ce, though I think you can easily imagine the look your lawyer would give y=
ou if you asked her this question. I will say though that if you ask your b=
uddies this=C2=A0question, they would probably say =E2=80=9Coh absolutely y=
es that sounds like a good time,=E2=80=9D and I cannot really fault them.=
=C2=A0Rolling around in a bathtub of money that you stole from the governme=
nt really is funny. Anyway here=E2=80=99s Bloomberg=E2=80=99s David Voreaco=
s with   one of the great first paragraphs of financial journalism:
Gary Harmon grinned as he lounged in a bathtub full of dollar bills surroun=
ded by scantily clad women. The moment, captured in a photo on his cellphon=
e, could be part of his undoing. To US prosecutors, it=E2=80=99s evidence t=
hat he suddenly came into a lot of money.
I will buy what they are selling on this point. If you show me a picture of=
 a man sitting in a bathtub of dollar bills,
  [9]
=C2=A0I am definitely going to think =E2=80=9Cthis man acquired that money =
suddenly.=E2=80=9D You don=E2=80=99t grind away at a steady job for 40 year=
s and then have your retirement party in a bathtub full of your pension. A =
bathtub of money really does indicate suddenness. Voreacos goes on:

The prosecutors accuse Harmon of a very unusual crime: remotely swiping Bit=
coin stored on a computer device the government had already seized in anoth=
er case, brought against his older brother, Larry. As authorities watched h=
elplessly, 713 digital tokens=E2=80=94then worth almost $5 million=E2=80=94=
were somehow spirited away from the =E2=80=9Chardware wallet=E2=80=9D they =
were holding in an evidence locker.
Larry Harmon, who=E2=80=99s since pleaded guilty to laundering $311 million=
 through crypto transactions, swore up and down he wasn=E2=80=99t involved =
in the disappearing act. Instead, Larry, 39, pointed the finger at Gary, 30=
, and ultimately helped to nail him. Gary is in federal jail in Washington,=
 D.C., awaiting trial, and Larry is free on bail near Akron. The cases of t=
he Harmons=E2=80=94literal crypto bros=E2=80=94show how the IRS and the FBI=
 are succeeding in collecting evidence but still face challenges on the blo=
ckchain frontier. Authorities had to track digital money moving through a t=
angle of anonymous accounts to connect it to Larry. When they tried to seiz=
e it, they faced a problem: How do you put a fence around a quicksilver ass=
et such as Bitcoin?

Colloquially you can say that you have Bitcoin =E2=80=9Con=E2=80=9D a hardw=
are wallet or other computer storage device, like  the guy in Wales who thr=
ew his in a garbage dump and keeps getting publicity for his schemes to dig=
 it up. But really the hardware wallet just stores your private keys to one=
 or more Bitcoin addresses, and having those on a hardware wallet doesn=E2=
=80=99t stop you from also storing them somewhere else =E2=80=94=C2=A0on an=
other hardware wallet, in your iPhone notes app, on a Post-it note, by=C2=
=A0memorizing them (or by memorizing a seed phrase that can be used to gene=
rate the keys), etc.=C2=A0The lesson for the government is that if you arre=
st someone for Bitcoin crime and you seize his hardware wallet, you have no=
t seized his Bitcoin; you have just seized a hard drive, and he =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0or his brother, or anyone else =E2=80=94=C2=A0might have other ways t=
o access the Bitcoins. The way you seize the Bitcoins is by getting his pri=
vate keys =E2=80=94=C2=A0from the hardware wallet, or by asking him, or wha=
tever =E2=80=94=C2=A0and then transferring them to an address that=C2=A0you=
=C2=A0control, where you can be pretty sure that he and his friends do not =
have the keys.

