lays <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29264112.2755=
27/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMi0xNzk/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cC77dee5ff" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">settled with the SEC again</a>, this tim=
e for selling unregistered securities. It registered $20.8 billion of secur=
ities, and overshot that by roughly $16.37 billion. Just not particularly c=
lose at all. It is illegal to sell unregistered securities, and so Barclays=
 paid the SEC a $200 million fine.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It also separately had to make a =E2=80=9Cresc=
ission offer,=E2=80=9D meaning that it had to=C2=A0contact everyone who bou=
ght those extra securities and say =E2=80=9Chey, if you want your money bac=
k, let us know.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0Holders of roughly <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29264112.275527/aHR0cHM6Ly9ob21lLmJhcmNsYXlz=
