<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Not legal advice but</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If your older brother does some crime, and he =
collects his loot in Bitcoin, and the US government seizes his Bitcoin, and=
 you steal the Bitcoin back out from under the government=E2=80=99s nose, a=
nd you convert the Bitcoin into dollars, should you put the dollars into a =
bathtub and roll around in them=C2=A0while women dance around you and your =
buddy takes pictures on your=C2=A0phone? I am not your lawyer and I am not =
going to give you legal advice, though I think you can easily imagine the l=
ook your lawyer would give you if you asked her this question. I will say t=
hough that if you ask your <em>buddies</em> this=C2=A0question, they would =
probably say =E2=80=9Coh absolutely yes that sounds like a good time,=E2=80=
=9D and I cannot really fault them.=C2=A0Rolling around in a bathtub of mon=
ey that you stole from the government really is funny. Anyway here=E2=80=99=
s Bloomberg=E2=80=99s David Voreacos with <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/29264112.275527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMDMvZmVkcy1zZWl6ZWQtMzExbS1pbi1iaXRjb2luLWJ0Yy=
10aGUtY3J5cHRvLWhhY2tlci1zdG9sZS1pdC1iYWNrP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMDQyMl9NT05FWVNUV=
UZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAw=
NCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3d7d8b49" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">  one of the great first paragraphs of financial journalism</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gary Harmon grinned as he lounged =
in a bathtub full of dollar bills surrounded by scantily clad women. The mo=
ment, captured in a photo on his cellphone, could be part of his undoing. T=
o US prosecutors, it=E2=80=99s evidence that he suddenly came into a lot of=
 money.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I will buy what they are selling on this point=
. If you show me a picture of a man sitting in a bathtub of dollar bills,<a=
 class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-9" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpa=
rent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[9]</span>
</a>=C2=A0I am definitely going to think =E2=80=9Cthis man acquired that mo=
ney suddenly.=E2=80=9D You don=E2=80=99t grind away at a steady job for 40 =
years and then have your retirement party in a bathtub full of your pension=
. A bathtub of money really does indicate suddenness. Voreacos goes on:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The prosecutors accuse Harmon of a very unusua=
l crime: remotely swiping Bitcoin stored on a computer device the governmen=
t had already seized in another case, brought against his older brother, La=
rry. As authorities watched helplessly, 713 digital tokens=E2=80=94then wor=
th almost $5 million=E2=80=94were somehow spirited away from the =E2=80=9Ch=
ardware wallet=E2=80=9D they were holding in an evidence locker.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Larry Harmon, who=E2=80=99s since pleaded guil=
ty to laundering $311 million through crypto transactions, swore up and dow=
n he wasn=E2=80=99t involved in the disappearing act. Instead, Larry, 39, p=
ointed the finger at Gary, 30, and ultimately helped to nail him. Gary is i=
n federal jail in Washington, D.C., awaiting trial, and Larry is free on ba=
il near Akron. The cases of the Harmons=E2=80=94literal crypto bros=E2=80=
=94show how the IRS and the FBI are succeeding in collecting evidence but s=
till face challenges on the blockchain frontier. Authorities had to track d=
igital money moving through a tangle of anonymous accounts to connect it to=
 Larry. When they tried to seize it, they faced a problem: How do you put a=
 fence around a quicksilver asset such as Bitcoin?</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Colloquially you can say that you have Bitcoin=
 =E2=80=9Con=E2=80=9D a hardware wallet or other computer storage device, l=
ike <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29264112.27552=
7/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS9zZWFyY2g_cT1tYXR0K2xldmluZSt3YWxlcytnYXJiY=
WdlK2R1bXAmcmx6PTFDNUNIRkFfZW5VUzgwN1VTODA3Jm9xPW1hdHQrbGV2aW5lK3dhbGVzK2dh=
cmJhZ2UrZHVtcCZhcXM9Y2hyb21lLi42OWk1Ny4zNDE2ajFqNyZzb3VyY2VpZD1jaHJvbWUmaWU=
9VVRGLTg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB472a3ebd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the guy in Wales</a> w=
ho threw his in a garbage dump and keeps getting publicity for his schemes =
to dig it up. But really the hardware wallet just stores your private keys =
to one or more Bitcoin addresses, and having those on a hardware wallet doe=
sn=E2=80=99t stop you from also storing them somewhere else =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
on another hardware wallet, in your iPhone notes app, on a Post-it note, by=
=C2=A0memorizing them (or by memorizing a seed phrase that can be used to g=
enerate the keys), etc.=C2=A0The lesson for the government is that if you a=
rrest someone for Bitcoin crime and you seize his hardware wallet, you have=
 not seized his Bitcoin; you have just seized a hard drive, and he =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0or his brother, or anyone else =E2=80=94=C2=A0might have other way=
s to access the Bitcoins. The way you seize the Bitcoins is by getting his =
private keys =E2=80=94=C2=A0from the hardware wallet, or by asking him, or =
whatever =E2=80=94=C2=A0and then transferring them to an address that=C2=A0=
<em>you=C2=A0</em>control, where you can be pretty sure that he and his fri=
ends do not have the keys.</p>
