<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/29264112.275527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMjMvYW1jLWdvZXMtYXBlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMDQyMl9NT05FWVNUV=
UZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAw=
NCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB440fa25a" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">  wrote in August</a> about Elon Musk=E2=80=99s efforts to get out of bu=
ying Twitter Inc.:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The situation is that the richest person in th=
e world, Elon Musk, has $44 billion riding on the question of whether Twitt=
er Inc. is doing a massive long-running fraud on its users, its advertisers=
 and its shareholders. Musk has claimed that it is, with no evidence at all=
, just a vague feeling that he has. If he=E2=80=99s right and there is a ma=
ssive fraud, then he can get out of his agreement to buy Twitter for about =
$44 billion. If he=E2=80=99s wrong, he has to buy Twitter.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This situation is extremely well known. There =
are incentives. If you have something to do with Twitter, or you know somet=
hing about Twitter, or you are in the business of counting Twitter bots, th=
en you should take a few minutes and ask yourself: Well, do I know anything=
 about Twitter doing any massive frauds? If you do =E2=80=A6 look, I don=E2=
=80=99t know exactly what you can do with that. I am not at all sure that y=
ou can actually go to Elon Musk and be like =E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99ve got a=
 pile of fraud documents, they=E2=80=99re yours for $1 billion.=E2=80=9D (H=
e could send you a subpoena and get them for free?) Even if you did strike =
a deal with him, he=E2=80=99s notoriously bad about sticking to his deals. =
Still. I just have a vague general sense that saving the richest person in =
the world $44 billion is a good career move.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So you should expect that, over the next month=
 or two, as Musk=E2=80=99s trial date with Twitter approaches, people will =
be popping up to say =E2=80=9Coh sure Twitter is a fraud, massive fraud, to=
tally, I have proof, Elon, call me.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well, that case goes to trial this month, and =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29264112.275527/aH=
R0cHM6Ly9ueXBvc3QuY29tLzIwMjIvMTAvMDMvc2Vjb25kLXR3aXR0ZXItd2hpc3RsZWJsb3dlc=
i1jb3VsZC1hcHBlYXItYXQtZWxvbi1tdXNrLXRyaWFsLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbf3f=
dff7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;"> here=E2=80=99s this</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another Twitter whistleblower is considering t=
aking the stand when Elon Musk faces the company in court over his $44 bill=
ion buyout deal later in two weeks =E2=80=94 and he may have a few things t=
o say about bots, The Post has learned. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The would-be whistleblower, a former Twitter e=
mployee, claims to have been involved in an internal report several years a=
go that supposedly concluded that at least 30% of Twitter=E2=80=99s daily a=
ctive users are automated spam accounts.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CTwitter execs laughed when they were =
told about the report and said, =E2=80=98We have always had a bot problem,=
=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D the potential whistleblower said in an interview with Th=
e Post. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The potential whistleblower said that Twitter=
=E2=80=99s chosen metric to measure bots =E2=80=94 called Monetizable Daily=
 Active Users, or mDAUs =E2=80=94 is overly narrow and fails to fully captu=
re the extent of the site=E2=80=99s spam problem. He said Twitter may not b=
e lying when it says that less than 5% of its mDAUs are bots, but takes iss=
ue with using mDAU as a measurement in the first place and claims the compa=
ny has not been transparent with investors.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yes look if he testifies that Twitter=E2=80=99=
s securities filings were accurate, but he didn=E2=80=99t <em>like=C2=A0</e=
m>them, then that won=E2=80=99t help Musk very much will it. The problem he=
re is that the incentives are so large and well-known that they will attrac=
t a lot of people who are eager to help but have nothing to offer.</p>
